sal or deliberate disclosure of data, among other issues. Conceptually designed by the activist Dutch design group Metahaven, this overscaled dense catalog is packed with images, artistic statements and scientific essays from both exhibitions, including outlines of all the contributions to this substantial project. Using mapping and fragmentation to convey the ubiquity of silent surveillance, the book is a complex and provocative contribution to this ever-present social dilemma. Contributions by Emmanuel Alloa, Neïl Beloufa, Clare Birchall , Juliette Blightman, Ryan Gander, Calla Henkel, Max Pitegoff, David Horvitz, Metahaven, Katja Novitskova, Yuri Pattison and Manfred Schneider.',1),(694,'','','Formy Zamieszkiwania: publiczne i prywatne przestrzenie miasta','','Uniwersytet Artstyczny w Poznani',NULL,2010,'Wolynski Piotr, ed.','','eastern european','E.EUR001','','formy-zamieszkiwania-publiczne-i-prywatne-przestrzenie-miasta','2016-12-23 22:01:27','2017-06-12 10:28:06',7,'0192203059651.jpg','image/jpeg',106599,389,500,'',3),(695,'3-932754-87-5','','Fluxus East: Fluxus Networks in Central Eastern Europe','DE/EN','Kunstlerhaus Bethanien',281,2007,'Petra Stegmann','Exhibition catalogue','','E.EUR002','','fluxus-east-fluxus-networks-in-central-eastern-europe','2016-12-23 22:01:27','2017-06-12 10:29:03',7,'9783932754876-us.jpg','image/jpeg',28622,343,500,'',1),(696,NULL,'978-9955-18-561-1','Menininkų kūrybos centrai ir jų bendruomenės Vidurio ir Rytų Europoje','LT/DE','Klaipėdos universiteto leidykla',160,2011,'Lina Motuzienė, Živilė Etevičiūtė',NULL,NULL,'E.EUR003',NULL,'menininku-kurybos-centrai-ir-ju-bendruomenes-vidurio-ir-rytu-europoje','2016-12-23 22:01:27','2016-12-23 22:13:50',7,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1),(697,'1-84638-005-7','','East Art Map: Contemporary Art and Eastern Europe','EN','Afterall',527,2006,'IRWIN, ed.','','','E.EUR004','','east-art-map-contemporary-art-and-eastern-europe','2016-12-23 22:01:27','2017-06-12 10:30:10',7,'9781846380051.jpg','image/jpeg',34827,365,475,'',1),(698,NULL,NULL,'Ha Kypopt!: русское искуство сегодня','RU','Кунстхалле, Баден- Баден, Винанд',158,2003,'Georgy Nikich, Mattias Vinsen',NULL,NULL,'E.EUR005',NULL,'ha-kypopt','2016-12-23 22:01:27','2016-12-23 22:13:50',7,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1),(699,NULL,'978-9986-957-48-5','Opening the Door?: Belarussian Art Today','EN/LT/RU','ŠMC/CAC',142,2011,'Julija Fomina, Kęstutis Kuizinas, eds.',NULL,NULL,'E.EUR006 ',NULL,'opening-the-door-belarussian-art-today','2016-12-23 22:01:27','2016-12-24 15:00:18',7,'51T2A4xksXL.jpg','image/jpeg',38587,327,500,'This exhibition is the first presentation of Belarusian contemporary artists in Lithuania to date. Despite the fact that Minsk, the capital city of Belarus, is situated only 170 kilometres (south) east of Vilnius, trade and cultural exchange between Lithuania and Belarus in the last twenty years has been slow, due to the current political situation in Belarus and exceptionally pro-western orientation of goals and perspectives of Lithuania.\n\n\n\"Opening the Door? Belarusian Art Today\" presents both artists living and working in Belarus as well as those residing abroad. It is not the first time that both halves of a disconnected art scene are being presented in a united project, but significantly it is being held in the closest proximity to its country of origin. Most of the Belarusian artists living in the West keep in touch with their families and make regular visits home, but seldom have they an opportunity to present their work in Minsk (or Belarus, generally). \n\nThis exhibition attempts to provide Belarusians with a possibility to look at their art from the outsider\'s perspective, without common taboos. Most of the works in the project, in one or another way, reflect upon Belarusian society and its concerns today, but only a few dare to openly express things that \'we don\'t talk about\'. \n\n\"Opening the Door? Belarusian Art Today\" is accompanied by a catalogue in Lithuanian, Russian and English and a conference at which Lithuanian and Belarusian researchers will present on the broader context of Belarusian contemporary art and culture.\n\nArtists: Anna Chkolnikova, Lena Davidovich, Oxana Gourinovitch, Artur Klinau, Aleksander Komarov, Alexander Korablev, Aleksej Lunev, Marina Naprushkina, Igor Peshehonov, Positive Actions, Igor Savchenko, Sergey Shabohin, Aleksei Shinkarenko, Philippe Tschmyr ir Belarusian Climate, Vladimir Tsesler ir Sergey Voichenko, Maxim Tyminko, Ruslan Vashkevich, Oleg Yushko',1),(700,'','978-9949-15-013-7','Postsovkhoz 1-6: An Anthology of MoKS International Art Symposium','EE/EN','MoKS',125,2007,'Evelyn Muursepp, John Grzinich, Jane Remm, eds.','','','E.EUR007','','postsovkhoz-1-6-an-anthology-of-moks-international-art-symposium','2016-12-23 22:01:27','2017-06-12 10:31:06',7,'postsovkhoz-1-6-moksi-20010.jpg','image/jpeg',139999,612,600,'',1),(701,NULL,NULL,'Meeting Place: north-european contemporary art','EN','Culture Centre Bla Stallet',76,2002,'Truls Olin, Konstantinas Bogdanas, Anna Roos, Ieva Cinite, Hanno Soans, Catherine Aiha','2 pcs.',NULL,'E.EUR008',NULL,'meeting-place-north-european-contemporary-art','2016-12-23 22:01:27','2016-12-23 22:13:50',7,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1),(702,NULL,NULL,'Russian Red','RU/EN','Kaliningrad branch of the NCCA',NULL,NULL,'Yuri Vasiliev ','postcards collection',NULL,'E.EUR009',NULL,'russian-red','2016-12-23 22:01:27','2016-12-23 22:13:50',7,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1),(703,NULL,NULL,'Tower Kronprinz: Second Advent','RU/EN','Kaliningrad branch of the NCCA',NULL,2006,'Elena Tsvetaeva, ed.','postcards collection',NULL,'E.EUR010',NULL,'tower-kronprinz-second-advent','2016-12-23 22:01:27','2016-12-26 12:20:37',7,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1),(704,NULL,'978-9949-18-666-2','Hotell Parnu. Rael Artel Gallery. Non-profit project space 2004-2008','EE/EN','Rael Artel Gallery',191,2009,'Rael Artel',NULL,NULL,'E.EUR011',NULL,'hotell-parnu-rael-artel-gallery-non-profit-project-spac