 we learn to read, and who wrestle with pathologies such as dyslexia. Like Steven Pinker, Dehaene argues that the mind is not a blank slate: Writing systems across all cultures rely on the same brain circuits, and reading is only possible insofar as it fits within the limits of a primate brain. Setting cutting-edge science in the context of cultural debate, &lt;i&gt;Reading in the Brain&lt;/i&gt; is an unparalleled guide to a uniquely human ability.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;',1),(874,'0-679-73739-1',NULL,'Monster in a Box','EN','Vintage Books',81,1992,'Spalding Gray ',NULL,NULL,'MISC047','John W. Fail','monster-in-a-box','2016-12-23 22:01:28','2016-12-24 14:14:23',22,'51Z2LxQxPCL.jpg','image/jpeg',48926,348,500,'The oddity that was Spaulding Gray is expressed in this book',1),(875,'0 330 29947 6',NULL,'Swimming to Cambodia','EN','Pan Books',304,1986,'Spalding Gray ',NULL,NULL,'MISC048','John W. Fail','swimming-to-cambodia','2016-12-23 22:01:28','2016-12-23 22:40:50',22,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1),(876,'0-922915-19-9',NULL,'Kooks','EN','Feral House Portland',253,1994,'Donna Kossy ',NULL,NULL,'MISC049','John W. Fail','kooks','2016-12-23 22:01:28','2016-12-23 22:40:50',22,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1),(877,NULL,NULL,'Charmed Circle','EN','Avon Books',640,1975,'James R. Mellow',NULL,NULL,'MISC050','John W. Fail','charmed-circle','2016-12-23 22:01:28','2016-12-23 22:13:51',22,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1),(878,'9-780922-915057',NULL,'Apocalypse Culture','EN','Feral House Portland',362,1990,'Adam Parfrey ',NULL,NULL,'MISC051','John W. Fail','apocalypse-culture','2016-12-23 22:01:28','2016-12-24 14:14:26',22,'51StTXeNF8L.jpg','image/jpeg',48660,310,500,'&lt;div&gt;\"Parfrey has edited a new book of Revelation, a collection which is almost as awesome and terrifying as the original biblical text.\"&lt;BR&gt;--Edwin Pouncey, NME&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;\"&lt;I&gt;Apocalypse Culture&lt;/I&gt; is compulsory reading for all those concerned with the crisis of our time